Enum Class MergeFunction

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Enum<MergeFunction>
org.krmdemo.techlabs.core.utils.MergeFunction
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Comparable<MergeFunction>, Constable
public enum MergeFunction extends Enum<MergeFunction>
This enumeration is used to handle the entries with the same key, when the stream of entries are collected into linked map or sorted map.

  • Enum Constant Details

    • OVERWRITE

      public static final MergeFunction OVERWRITE
      The default merging-function, that emulates the behaviour of consecutive invocation of the method put(key,value) with the same key. So, the last entry with same key overwrites the values of all previous ones.

    • IGNORE

      public static final MergeFunction IGNORE
      This merging-function ignores any subsequent attempts to overwrite the existing value for the same key. So, the first entry with same key remains in the result map.

    • THROW

      public static final MergeFunction THROW
      This merging-function guarantees that the source stream does not contain entries with the same keys. Otherwise, an IllegalStateException is thrown on the first attempt to violate that.
